# UI Component Usage

Always reach for an existing component from `~/shared/ui/` before writing custom markup. Add only the minimum Tailwind classes needed on top ‚Äî never re-implement what the component already provides.

## Available components

`Button`, `Badge`, `Card`, `Tabs`, `Tooltip`, `Popover`, `Switch`, `Avatar`, `TextField`, `AlertDialog`

## Rules

- **Use first, style second**: import from `~/shared/ui/`, then layer extra classes via `cn()` only when truly needed.
- **No parallel implementations**: don't recreate a button, badge, card, etc. with plain `<div>`/`<span>` when a shared component exists.
- **Extend via props**: prefer the component's own props (variant, size, ‚Ä¶) over overriding with Tailwind.
- **`cn()` for overrides**: when you must add classes, always merge them with `cn()`.

```tsx
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî reimplements an existing component
<div class="rounded-full bg-primary px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold text-primary-foreground">
  New
</div>

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî uses the shared Badge, one extra class only
import { Badge } from '~/shared/ui/badge'

<Badge variant="default" class={cn('mt-1')}>New</Badge>
```

## Design Token Usage

Always use theme tokens ‚Äî never hardcode raw colors, shadows, or gradients.

**Lookup order:**
1. Check `tailwind.config.js` (`theme.extend`) for an existing token.
2. Check `src/app/styles/index.css` (`:root` / `.dark`) for an existing CSS variable.
3. If nothing fits, **add** a new CSS variable in `index.css` **and** expose it in `tailwind.config.js`, then use the new token.

### Available tokens

| Category | Tailwind class examples | CSS variable |
|---|---|---|
| Colors | `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, `bg-accent`, `text-destructive`, `bg-info`, `bg-success`, `bg-warning`, `bg-error` | `--primary`, `--muted-foreground`, ‚Ä¶ |
| Shadows | `shadow-surface`, `shadow-elevated`, `shadow-overlay`, `shadow-container` | `--shadow-surface`, ‚Ä¶ |
| Gradients | `bg-page` | `--gradient-page` |
| Radius | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl` | `--radius` |

```tsx
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî hardcoded values bypass the theme
<div style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(143deg, #f8fafc, #f1f5f9)', boxShadow: '0 4px 6px rgb(0 0 0 / .1)' }} />

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî uses existing theme tokens
<div class="bg-page shadow-elevated" />

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî no existing token ‚Üí add one first, then use it
// 1. src/app/styles/index.css  ‚Üí  --gradient-hero: linear-gradient(...);
// 2. tailwind.config.js        ‚Üí  backgroundImage: { hero: 'var(--gradient-hero)' }
// 3. JSX                       ‚Üí  <div class="bg-hero" />
```
